Interface Atom<T extends Atom>

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Subinterfaces:
AnalysisSet, Group, LazyMolSet<S,T>, Molecule<T>, MolSetInterface<S,T>, Reference, ReferenceSet, TagSet
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractInMemorySet, AbstractMolSet, Analysis, AtomImpl, Feature, FeatureList, FeatureSet, InMemoryAnalysisSet, InMemoryFeatureSet, InMemoryGroup, InMemoryQueryFutureImpl, InMemoryReference, InMemoryReferenceSet, InMemoryTagSet, LazyFeatureSet, MoleculeImpl, MRLazyFeatureSet, Tag, User
public interface Atom<T extends Atom>
extends Taggable, Versionable<T>, Serializable, Buildable

Implements core functionality that is shared by all classes that require tags. Deriving Feature and FeatureSet from one base class facilitates code re-use for interface implementations that are shared by those classes.

Author:
jbaran, dyuen
